isValid

public static boolean isValid(Annotation annotation)
                       throws PatternSyntaxException
Determine if the given Annotation is valid. A valid Annotation is one in which its value is valid for its defined AnnotationDefinition.

Parameters:
annotation - the Annotation to validate. This Annotation must return a non-null AnnotationDefinition for Annotation.getDefinition().
Returns:
whether the Annotation is valid
Throws:
PatternSyntaxException - if the AnnotationDefinition used by the Annotation is of type and the specified pattern is invalid.
See Also:
isValid(AnnotationDefinition, String)

isValid

public static boolean isValid(AnnotationDefinition annoDef,
                              String value)
                       throws PatternSyntaxException
Determine if the given value is valid as defined by the specified AnnotationDefinition. A valid value is one that is valid for the specified domain of the AnnotationDefinition.

Parameters:
annoDef - a non-null AnnotationDefinition. Although the AnnotationType of the annoDef may be null, this method will always evaluate to false in such a case.
value - the value to validate, possibly null
Returns:
whether the given value is valid as defined by the given AnnotationDefinition
Throws:
PatternSyntaxException - if the AnnotationDefinition used by the Annotation is of type and the specified pattern is invalid.
InvalidArgument - Thrown if the annoDef argument isnull
